<H3>Aura_fullpath</H3>
</div>
<p>Creates the absolute path name for the specified relative path name.</p>
<div class="proto">
<TABLE cellspacing="3" cellpadding="2" style="font-size:90%">
<TR valign="top">
<TD colspan="5" class="datatype">EXTERN_C wchar_t* CDECL Aura_fullpath
                    (
                 </TD>
</TR>
<TR valign="top">
<TD width="8%"></TD>
<TD class="datatype">char*</TD>
<TD class="param">absPath<span style="color:black; font-size:110%">,</span></TD>
</TR>
<TR valign="top">
<TD width="8%"></TD>
<TD class="datatype">const char*</TD>
<TD class="param">relPath<span style="color:black; font-size:110%">,</span></TD>
</TR>
<TR valign="top">
<TD width="8%"></TD>
<TD class="datatype">size_t</TD>
<TD class="param">maxLength.</TD>
</TR>
<TR>
<TD colspan="5" class="datatype">);</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
</div>
<br />
<H4>Parameters</H4>
<DL><DT class="param" style="color:#222222;margin-left:42">absPath</DT>
<DD style="margin-left:80"><font style="font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;color:black">Pointer to a buffer containing the absolute path.<BR /><BR />
</font></DD>
<DT class="param" style="color:#222222;margin-left:42">relPath</DT>
<DD style="margin-left:80"><font style="font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;color:black">Pointer to a character string storing the relative path.<BR /><BR />
</font></DD>
<DT class="param" style="color:#222222;margin-left:42">maxLength.</DT>
<DD style="margin-left:80"><font style="font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;color:black">Size of the buffer.<BR /><BR />
</font></DD>
</DL>
<DL></DL>
<h4>Return Value</h4>
<p>If there is no error, each of these functions returns a pointer to a buffer containing the absolute path name, otherwise(for example, if the value passed in relPath 
              includes a drive letter that is not valid or can not be found; or if the length of the absolute path name is greater than maxLength)the function returns NULL.</p>
<h4>Remarks</h4>
<p>The _fullpath function expands the relative path in 'relPath' to the absolute path and stores this name in 'absPath'. Relative path name describes another path name corresponding to the current location(such as the current working directory: "."). An absolute path name is the expansion of relative path name and its beginning is the root of the file system.
              _fullpath can be used to obtain the absolute path name for relative paths that include "./" or "../" in their names.</p>
<p>_wfullpath is a wide-character version of _fullpath. The character strings declared in _wfullpath are wide-character strings.</p>
<p>If the absPath buffer is NULL, _fullpath calls 
malloc</a> function to allocate a buffer of size _MAX_PATH and ignores the maxLength argument, then returns the pointer to the buffer. It's the caller's responsibility to free the memory of the buffer as appropriate(call 
free</a> function). if the relative 
              path specifies a disk drive, then the current directory of this drive is combined with the path.</p>
